What you need to know:  At 25, Kosgei joined the enviable club of world record holders when she shattered the 16-year-old record held by British legend Paula Radcliffe at the Chicago Marathon in 2019She took part in her first international race, the Porto Novo Marathon in Italy, in 2016 and emerged the surprise winner despite being a newcomer in the marathon raceCoach Kimaiyo said that Kosgei has climbed up the ladder in a steady manner due to her hard work in training which has always yielded good results